# HOME-REPOSITORY SAFETY POLICY
#
# This repository's worktree is the entire home directory, so these sections
# intentionally convert the usual blacklist-style .gitignore into a default-
# deny allowlist. Git uses the LAST matching rule, making the order below part
# of the safety policy:
#
#   1. Rules above this block exclude known data, caches, generated files, and
#      secrets. They also document why those paths do not belong in Git.
#   2. The two catch-all rules below deny every otherwise-unmatched top-level
#      path. Existing tracked files are unaffected.
#   3. The `!` rules after the catch-alls admit only approved configuration and
#      tooling categories. Stateful/sensitive roots must re-ignore everything
#      first, then allow only specific durable files.
#   4. Permanent safety exclusions stay LAST. Do not put `!` rules after them.
#
# Do not move the catch-all rules to the top without redesigning every later
# exception: older `!` rules would then be able to weaken the default-deny
# boundary. To admit a new category, add the narrowest possible `!` rule in the
# allowlist section, before the permanent-exclusions section. Prefer that over
# `git add -f`; if forcing is unavoidable, force only the exact intended path.
/*
/.*

# APPROVED GENERAL CATEGORIES
# New files in these directories are eligible for normal `git add`; more
# sensitive roots remain selective below.
!/bin/
!/test/
!/.config/
/.config/*
!/.config/git/
!/.config/htop/
!/.config/nvim

!/.config/gh/
/.config/gh/*
!/.config/gh/config.yml

!/.config/karabiner/
/.config/karabiner/*
!/.config/karabiner/karabiner.json

!/.github/
!/.iterm2/
!/.cask-emacs.d/

# APPROVED SELECTIVE CATEGORIES
# Track only durable configuration within stateful or sensitive roots. Each
# parent is admitted so Git can traverse it, then its contents are denied and
# narrowly re-admitted.
!/.codex/
/.codex/**
!/.codex/config.toml
# Global Codex instructions; instructions.md is not a default instruction file.
!/.codex/AGENTS.md

!/.ssh/
/.ssh/**
!/.ssh/config
!/.ssh/allowed_signers

!/.unison/
/.unison/*
!/.unison/*.prf

# Keep the diagnostic GUI-environment utility reproducible without admitting
# other applications installed under ~/Applications.
!/Applications/
/Applications/*
!/Applications/env-gui-macos.app/

# PERMANENT SAFETY EXCLUSIONS -- KEEP THIS SECTION LAST
# Nothing below this block may negate these rules. In particular, the home
# repository must never recursively ingest its own object database.
/.dotfiles-git-dir/
